Asynchronously makes a query to an SQL server. The profile, query, and params arguments work the same as %s, so see the documentation of that function for details about those parameters. The callback should have the following signature: closure(@contents, @exception){ <code> }. @contents will contain the return value that query would normally return. If @exception is not %s, then an exception occurred during the query, and that exception will be passed in. If @exception is %s, then no error occured, though @contents may still be %s if query() would otherwise have returned %s.
